%
% v3.19: Revert page-eject ghost narrowing fix (Task 169).
%   v3.18's page-eject (insert \newpage when nl*bs > remaining-2*bs)
%   REGRESSED ghost narrowing from 4 to 11 on 50-page test (3x worse).
%   Root cause: \newpage did not reset parshape/text-width state from
%   previous figures. The ejected page started with leaked parshape,
%   creating new ghost-narrowed pages that didn't exist before.
%   FIX: Revert page-eject entirely. In post_linebreak_filter, when
%   total_lines < nl (paragraph broke across pages within narrow zone),
%   zero out remaining@nl to prevent everypar from re-applying parshape
%   to subsequent paragraphs. The leaked parshape lines on the
%   continuation page are a fundamental TeX limitation — parshape is
%   assigned before page breaking. Penalty at boundary (v3.6) remains
